  "response": "Whether a prime minister requires a visa to visit another country depends on diplomatic agreements and visa policies between their country and the destination country. In many cases, prime ministers and other high-ranking officials may enjoy visa exemptions or expedited visa processes due to diplomatic arrangements or as part of official state visits. However, this can vary significantly depending on the countries involved.\n\nPlease specify the countries you're interested in for more detailed information on their specific diplomatic arrangements and visa requirements.",
